column5: Yes, we're diehards, the fishing has been so good we'd like to do one more trip (at least). A Remembrance Day to remember. Is the Winnipeg River and Traverse Bay still open? Thanks.

Yes , This year it may stay open to December? I have fished up to Nov 23 & Some of my friends have gone well into December. One friend was there yesterday & caught close to 70 fish , the best one topping 27"

Yes the lake is still open and should remain that way until we see colder weather. Heading out on Lake Winnipeg this morning. The plans are to mark a few waypoints for the fast appproaching hard water season and of coarse to see if we can locate and catch a few 'eyes during the process. Good-Luck on the weekend.
A man who lives 500km north of Edmonton phoned me Saturday. He said they have no ice or snow and temps have been near 10c recently. The ice roads will have a short season from the looks of it.
a freind of mine was out today still wide open
heading up sunday have fished it as late as dec 8th lots of time left..... manitoba .... a 100,000 lakes how many walleyes ???? i will never have enough time....
it was great i used it one time and it was stolen and recovered less the Verado about 10miles from my house in a back lane
Wow Now what going to happen? Is the boat damage ??
